<br>
- Seahorses are either clerics or wizards, the clerics cheal. The wizards are easy, but the clerics are a pain (pet can't solo them either, maybe epic, but not vocerates, so you can't just wear down their mana).<br>
<br>
- Kill enough seahorses and a tainted one will spawn (for the druid epic). Tainted will spawn a corrupted seahorse when killed, they're both clerics. The tainted isn't too bad, but the corrupted is pretty tough. I think more than one tainted can be up at once, so don't think you could just get him to spawn in some out of the way spot, then kill the rest.<br>
<br>
Now add a couple people, and these are all easy to handle, but solo it's rough. But then I was hoping to find something to do down there while I assemble hunting parties.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the other info though. How tough is the seahorse patriarch room ? I'd thought about trying it, but wasn't anxious to try seahorses solo.<br>
<br>
