 <p><center> <img src=http://members.aol.com/lordgrome/fallbala.gif> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#333333>(5/3/02 2:14:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solo'ing in Kedge ?</span><hr size=1> No, AE's in Kedge are VERY bad. Those little green sailfin fish you see swimming around all over the place ? Well, when they die, they can explode doing up to 500 damage. Just wouldn't risk them myself.<br>
<br>
Pulling in Kedge is a royal pain for a mage I've found. According to a monk friend of mine, whose pulled Kedge quite a few times, aggro'ing mobs from a distance with spells and whatnot is a pretty bad idea. He reccomends a technique he called aggro pulling, basiclly just inch towards a mob till your just close enough to aggro it and run back to your pull spot. Problem I have with this method, I usually wind up with the mob warping on top of me, or hitting me with a spell and the pet will pop right on top of the mob. Anything close by of course adds into the fight. Times like these, /pet hold would be really nice, but of course we must pay for bug fixes (no, I'm not bitter, not one bit).<br>
<br>
As for the temple, there is a pretty safe spot you can pull to. Let's see if I can describe this. On either side of Estrella's room are smaller rooms where a couple mermaid's spawn. One side leads to Phinny, and the opposite side leads to the temple (and you get there through the fallen grate). Anyways, there's a ledge there with a tube leading to the temple. There's no roamers there, and your out of aggro range of any of the mermaids (just don't get too close to the ledge). Good spot to buff up and med for fights, also good to pull the pirrahna, mermaid, and roaming seahorse here, then moving up. Just outside the temple on the left (facing looking into the temple) is a little area with some pillars. This is a good spot to pull seahorses too, but don't setup here due to the roamer (unless you can take him with a minimum of buffs and mana). Good reason to pull to here is it's a shorter distance, less stupid crap can happen.<br>
<br>
Still haven't been back to try out any of the other areas solo. <br>
<br>
Kinelaria <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udede9002.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dede9002</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(5/3/02 4:04:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solo'ing in Kedge ?</span><hr size=1> On AE : this is just my style i love AEs but i wouldnt recommend them indeed.<br>
<br>
Pull spots : <br>
-This ledge is in front of balcony and is indeed a good one, trouble is this place have spawn spots to trouble you during your pulls and another one pops quite close and can agro while fighting if you dont care. Or you have to get a bit behind and then its a hell to pull to the place (the one leading to fallen gate) mostly when you pull mermaids (casters) with a pet.<br>
- Tunnel between sharks and patriarch : my fav' because no roamers, close camps. I always end up fighting in my tunnel and have no adds and pet never have time to agro elsewhere.<br>
<br>
Pulling technics : <br>
- My Pulling in KK is like you cast on a mob, you run away, mob doesnt follow he just pops on you... its quite annoying cause you always get hit but at least its safe as keepin a pull spot. (Just try and avoid to have long pulls if you pull casters or youre pet will end up charging)<br>
- Agro pulling : only good for melees really you will definately get hit before getting back to pull spot and you dont want to fight in the middle of a roaming potential place... so if you dont have a melee friend with you pull with spells. <br>
Only trouble with spells is pulling in a bigger area like Undertow's because pillars make them unpop... and as pulling with spells they may chose a bad pathing and end up poofing...<br>
<br>
In those places agro pull is ok if you accept to fight where you dont want to. Another idea is to park pet FAR AWAY from agro range and agro pull then summon him to you... can work just dont fizzle too mucho <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
